`` I Believe '' is a popular song written by Ervin Drake , Irvin Graham , Jimmy Shirl and Al Stillman in 1953 .
`` I Believe '' was commissioned and introduced by Jane Froman on her television show , and became the first hit song ever introduced on TV .
Froman , troubled by the uprising of the Korean War in 1952 so soon after World War II , asked Drake , Graham , Shirl and Stillman to compose a song that would offer hope and faith to the populace .
In addition to Froman , `` I Believe '' has been recorded by many others , and has become both a popular and religious standard .
Frankie Laine 's version spent eighteen non-consecutive weeks at the top of the UK Singles Chart .
Laine also had the most successful version in America , where he reached # 2 for three weeks .